.github/workflows/release.yml:7:  build-and-release:
.github/workflows/release.yml:13:      EXPECTED_SIGNING_IDENTITY: "Developer ID Application: AUTIMO SYSTEMS INC (HMR9RDR6M2)"
.github/workflows/release.yml:61:      - name: Audit release signing and publishing assumptions
.github/workflows/release.yml:66:          RELEASE_WORKFLOW=".github/workflows/release.yml"
.github/workflows/release.yml:72:          if grep -Eq 'CODE_SIGN_IDENTITY = "?Developer ID Application"?;' "$PROJECT_FILE"; then
.github/workflows/release.yml:73:            echo "::error::Project contains generic Developer ID Application signing identity"
.github/workflows/release.yml:77:          if grep -Eq 'CODE_SIGN_IDENTITY = "?Developer ID Application"?;' "$RELEASE_WORKFLOW"; then
.github/workflows/release.yml:78:            echo "::error::Release workflow contains generic Developer ID Application signing identity"
.github/workflows/release.yml:82:          TEAM_SECRET_NAME="APPLE_TEAM_ID"
.github/workflows/release.yml:99:          echo "- GitHub release creation with contents:write permission"
.github/workflows/release.yml:100:          echo "- Homebrew tap clone, commit, and push with HOMEBREW_TAP_TOKEN"
.github/workflows/release.yml:221:        uses: softprops/action-gh-release@v3
.github/workflows/release.yml:228:          prerelease: false
.github/workflows/release.yml:248:          git push
README.md:69:1. Download the latest Pinemeter release from [GitHub Releases](https://github.com/eddmann/Pinemeter/releases/latest).
README.md:73:Releases are signed and notarized. If you validate release artifacts manually, the expected Developer ID is `Developer ID Application: AUTIMO SYSTEMS INC (HMR9RDR6M2)` and the expected Team Identifier is `HMR9RDR6M2`.
README.md:237:Read [RELEASING.md](RELEASING.md) before preparing release artifacts. The release path must use the pinned Autimo signing identity `Developer ID Application: AUTIMO SYSTEMS INC (HMR9RDR6M2)` and verify `TeamIdentifier=HMR9RDR6M2`; generic `Developer ID Application` signing identities and mutable `APPLE_TEAM_ID`-style secrets are unsafe for release signing.
README.md:239:Safe local checks are limited to reading local files or locally built artifacts, such as verifying the pinned `CODE_SIGN_IDENTITY`, `DEVELOPMENT_TEAM`, workflow `EXPECTED_SIGNING_IDENTITY`, workflow `EXPECTED_TEAM_ID`, and `codesign -dvv` output. Publishing or remote mutations require explicit maintainer confirmation for the intended version and target repository, including workflow dispatch, notarization submission, GitHub release creation, Homebrew tap edits, `git push`, tag changes, `gh release`, or history rewriting.
RELEASING.md:3:This document describes the safe local checks to run before triggering the manual release workflow. It intentionally separates non-destructive verification from steps that publish artifacts or mutate remote repositories.
RELEASING.md:9:- Signing identity: `Developer ID Application: AUTIMO SYSTEMS INC (HMR9RDR6M2)`
RELEASING.md:10:- Expected Team Identifier: `TeamIdentifier=HMR9RDR6M2`
RELEASING.md:13:Do not replace this with the generic `Developer ID Application` identity. Do not introduce a mutable `APPLE_TEAM_ID` or similar secret for release signing; the release path must continue to pin and verify the Autimo team identifier explicitly.
RELEASING.md:17:These checks read local files or local build artifacts only. They do not push commits, create GitHub releases, update the Homebrew tap, notarize, or publish anything.
RELEASING.md:19:### Check pinned release configuration
RELEASING.md:22:EXPECTED_SIGNING_IDENTITY="Developer ID Application: AUTIMO SYSTEMS INC (HMR9RDR6M2)"
RELEASING.md:27:grep -F "EXPECTED_SIGNING_IDENTITY: \"$EXPECTED_SIGNING_IDENTITY\"" .github/workflows/release.yml
RELEASING.md:28:grep -F "EXPECTED_TEAM_ID: $EXPECTED_TEAM_ID" .github/workflows/release.yml
RELEASING.md:31:### Check a built release artifact locally
RELEASING.md:33:After a local release build exists at `build/Build/Products/Release/Pinemeter.app`, verify the signature details before considering any publishing step:
RELEASING.md:37:EXPECTED_SIGNING_IDENTITY="Developer ID Application: AUTIMO SYSTEMS INC (HMR9RDR6M2)"
RELEASING.md:48:For an installed or downloaded app, the same signature checks can be run against that `.app` path. The important release invariant is that `Authority=Developer ID Application: AUTIMO SYSTEMS INC (HMR9RDR6M2)` and `TeamIdentifier=HMR9RDR6M2` both appear in the `codesign -dvv` output.
RELEASING.md:52:The GitHub Actions release workflow is manual, but it is not just a local verification job. Once triggered with valid secrets, it can mutate remote state:
RELEASING.md:54:- Creates a GitHub release using `contents: write` and uploads the ZIP artifact.
RELEASING.md:55:- Clones, commits to, and runs `git push` against the Homebrew tap using `HOMEBREW_TAP_TOKEN`.
RELEASING.md:58:Do not trigger, re-run, or modify these publishing steps as a signing check. Publishing, `git push`, `gh release`, Homebrew tap updates, notarization submissions, tag changes, or history rewriting require explicit maintainer confirmation for the intended version and target repository.
RELEASING.md:62:If signing verification fails, inspect the failing surface before retrying any release:
RELEASING.md:64:1. Confirm `Pinemeter.xcodeproj/project.pbxproj` still contains `CODE_SIGN_IDENTITY = "Developer ID Application: AUTIMO SYSTEMS INC (HMR9RDR6M2)";` and `DEVELOPMENT_TEAM = HMR9RDR6M2;`.
RELEASING.md:65:2. Confirm `.github/workflows/release.yml` still exports `EXPECTED_SIGNING_IDENTITY` and `EXPECTED_TEAM_ID` with the official values.
RELEASING.md:66:3. Confirm the imported Apple certificate contains `Developer ID Application: AUTIMO SYSTEMS INC (HMR9RDR6M2)` before building.
RELEASING.md:67:4. Inspect `codesign -dvv` output for the produced app and verify `TeamIdentifier=HMR9RDR6M2`.
RELEASING.md:68:5. Treat any generic `Developer ID Application` match without `AUTIMO SYSTEMS INC (HMR9RDR6M2)` as unsafe for release artifacts.
RELEASING.md:70:Keep secrets out of logs and documentation. The release documentation should name required secret keys only when needed for diagnosis, never their values.
